I was luaghing the other night i decided to download a movie and the torrent hit almost 40 megabytes a second. i actually had to add more ram to the virtual machine coz tixati (torrent client) was running out of ram and buffer flushing causing the speed to drop to 0 every minute or so.

it was a abit of a road to get to that kind of speeds. there was issues with the antennas either been to close to eachother or to far from eachother. i had to read long borring forum threads about how MIMO works and different frequencies have different distances of the wavelength in IRL. the spacing is super important apparently for the frequency phase to align. some shit like that anyway.

Oh and then whenever i ran speed test over just 1 modem, id get like 200 or 300 ish megabit but over both itd only increase by a little so the result would be 350 to 400.... im like !!?? ended up using an app that can lock the band (frequency) in the modems so each modem is locked to a different band that both are supported by the carrier, one band is 15mhz wide and the other is 20mhz wide so one is a tad faster than the other. anyway now they are connected to different cells and dont slow eachother down.
